  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">DFID What Works to Prevent Violence: Impact at Scale (ABD Component)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In June 2019 the Secretary of State for International Development approved a new seven-year global programme: &apos;What Works to Prevent Violence &#x2013; Impact at Scale&apos;. This will be a successor to What Works to Prevent Violence (2013-19).  The overall programme will invest up to &#xA3;67.5 million over seven years to prevent and contribute to eliminating violence against women and girls (VAWG) through: systematically designing, implementing and rigorously evaluating the scale-up of violence prevention efforts; piloting and testing new theory-driven approaches; strengthening long-term capability, capacity and commitment to deliver cutting-edge violence prevention programmes across HMG and globally; and using evidence to influence a more effective global response. The programme has 4 components: A) scaling-up violence prevention, B) innovation, C) research and evaluation and D) programme leadership, technical assistance, capacity development and policy influencing. This G/NG is for component ABD (with a total envelope of &#xA3;45.5mil)</narrative>
  </description>
